==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: cyclosporine
<hw>cyclosporine</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>a chemical substance produced by some soil fungi, which suppresses
the cellular immune response by inhibiting T cell activation, and has
been used in medicine to reduce foreign tissue rejection, especially
subsequent to organ transplant surgery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

